{
  "texts": [
    "To account for this, we classify a commit as contributing to capability innovation (With Function Definition = 1) only if there is a positive net addition of functions across all files in the commit.",
    "Otherwise, the commit is classified as not contributing to capability innovation (Without Function Definition = 0).",
    "For each language, we develop specific parsers to identify function additions and removals.",
    "Function detection varies by language because of syntax differences.",
    "Python, R and Rust have relatively straightforward function definition patterns, whereas Haskell presents greater challenges as distinguishing between type signatures, method implementations, and actual function definitions requires complex pattern matching."
  ]
}